body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for reaching out to Car Dealership Support. My name is Frank Brown.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hello, my name is Tammy Collins.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Tammy Collins. How can I assist you today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I have a question about my recent car service.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Of course, Tammy. Can you please provide me with your vehicle's VIN number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's eight zero zero one two three four five six seven.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you. And may I also have your preferred contact number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Yes, it's six five zero five five five eight eight eight eight.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Tammy, for sharing the information. Is there anything else I can assist you with today?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for your time, Tammy Collins. Have a great day!
